b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Coda AI and Motion share a solid foundation of core features including Task Management, Ai Assistant, Collaboration, Automation. Where Coda AI pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Notes and Templates, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Motion uniquely offers Calendar, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Coda AI holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Motion scores 8/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Coda AI offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Motion's starting price of $34/mo. Coda AI has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Motion does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
